l":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz","html_url":"https://github.com/ulfllorenz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-04-15T13:50:11Z","updated_at":"2025-04-15T13:50:11Z","body":"Short form: I think the copyright from the license file is the \"most useful\" one.\n\nLong form: Consumers of Polly must deliver two pieces of information (clause 2 of BSD-3-Clause): The copyright and the disclaimer in the license file (in practice: something like the license file). In principle, I can think of three distinct ways of doing so (arbitrary mixtures possible):\n\n1. Extract Copyright and license from Nuget package, then look up, possibly generic, license text from license URL or SPDX identifier.\n2. Figure out that Polly is hosted on github, and query github API / Repo to get the license text and copyright.\n3. Take the license text supplied with the Nuget package.\n\nThey all have drawbacks. Nuget package metadata is too often bad, so 1. can only be a first attempt. Variant 2 requires infrastructure (network connections, github tokens, ...) and has some edge cases, i.e., is mostly for standard tooling. Variant 3 does not give you metadata, and requires a license file with the package.\n\nFor the best coverage, I would augment my original proposal to use the copyright from the license file (supports the first approach), and ship the license with the Nuget package (supports the third use-case).","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/App-vNext/Polly/issues/comments/2805128295/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ulfllorenz","id":68948878,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4OTQ4ODc4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/68948878?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz","html_url":"https://github.com/ulfllorenz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ulfllorenz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":17270185752,"node_id":"REFE_lADOAJaD5s6x9Nv7zwAAAAQFYh8Y","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/App-vNext/Polly/issues/events/17270185752","actor":{"login":"martincostello","id":1439341,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzkzNDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1439341?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello","html_url":"https://github.com/martincostello","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/gists{/gist_id}","starred_